{
  "stem": "22447.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was like a free evening or something.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And people used to conduct meetings on the street corners.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then sometimes, if you go down [? to my ?] [? chapel ?] two people start talking and then people gather around, then they start talking.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then the two people that started originally, they'd walk away and everybody was arguing [LAUGHS] amongst themselves.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was, during this period, I believe there was a lot of anti-Semitism in the areas around the East End.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, afterwards, like in '35, '36, then it became a bit more.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, in the East End, there was a fairly strong Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, it was only the time when the-- that the-- Moseley wanted to go through Cable Street in 1936.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were still in the East End, and everyone turned out to stop him, which they did.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, they used to go visiting people, you know, that you knew from the old country, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Everybody lived together.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From Poland.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1900s somewhere.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They got married in 1908 in [INAUDIBLE] Square Synagogue. 1908 they were married.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when war broke out, I got called up in 19-- February 5, 1940.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went for a medical in December, and then they sent-- I called them up, [INAUDIBLE] the post law, what they called the king's shilling, the time they gave-- they paid you to-- you got called up on Thursday and pay day was Friday so you got paid for one day.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you get what was called the king's shilling.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They sent you a post law that told me to report.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was fortunate.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
